{"id":"7118","name":"bright-early-remember-this-one-thing-edition","title":"Bright &amp; Early: Remember This One Thing Edition","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2011-05-13T09:30:00-05:00","tags":["28th avenue connector","belmont university","bomb threat","carson dunn","cicadas","gulch","jackalope brewing company","m street","nondiscrimination ordinance","north gulch","severe weather"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/16828091@N04/5712462249/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\"><img src=\"http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2579/5712462249_88bf1bc7de.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\"></a></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Good morning, Nashville. <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/mdha-ready-begin-444k-streetscape-work-north-gulch?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+NashvilleCityPaper-CityNews+%28Nashville+City+Paper+-+City+News%29&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">The city is getting ready to take on a big improvement project in the &#x201C;North Gulch&#x201D; which, as you might guess, is the area just north of the Gulch proper</a>. The area they&#x2019;re hoping to improve includes 12th Avenue South between Broadway and Demonbreun as well as McGavock Street between 11th and 13th avenues. Though the area is mostly railroad tracks and potholes at the moment, developers and restauranteurs have high hopes for sprucing it up, so Metro will be replacing sidewalks, repaving (maybe adding some lines to the road if we&#x2019;re lucky?) and adding some streetlights to make it more palatable. All in all, they&#x2019;re committing about $444,000 to the project.</p><ul><li><strong>Connect four. </strong>Speaking of development projects, <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/preliminary-work-underway-28th31st-avenue-connector?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+NashvilleCityPaper-CityNews+%28Nashville+City+Paper+-+City+News%29&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Metro has finally started building that 28th avenue connector they approved two years ago</a>. The new stretch of street will hopefully make it easier to get from West End to North Nashville more easily and encourage development along that part of Charlotte.</li><li><strong>Student arrested for bomb threat. </strong>Nineteen year-old Carson Dunn, a Belmont student, <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/story/14637493/student-arrested-for-recent-belmont-uni-bomb-threat\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">was arrested for calling in a bomb threat earlier this week that forced a partial evacuation of Belmont&#x2019;s campus</a>. And it&#x2019;s just as everyone suspected: Carson simply did not want to take his final exams.</li><li><strong>Bits &amp; pieces.</strong> <a href=\"http://nashvillewx.com/2011/05/storms-today-potentially-severe/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillewx.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Be on the lookout for some severe weather</a> this afternoon &#x2026;<a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20110513/NEWS/305130061/2275/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\"> Nashville&#x2019;s median age has dropped a bit in the past ten years</a> thanks to younger people moving into the city with small children &#x2026; <a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/story/14635774/2-women-behind-new-brewery-in-nashville\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Jackalope Brewing is expected to open within this next few weeks</a>. Read <a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2010/11/30/the-new-brew-on-the-block-meet-jackalope-brewing-company-nashville-newcomers/\" target=\"_blank\">our interview with the ladies in charge</a> from a few months back &#x2026; <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/state-senate-votes-nullify-metros-anti-gay-bias-ordinance?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+NashvilleCityPaper-LatestNews+%28Nashville+City+Paper+-+Latest+News%29&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">The bill that would nullify Nashville&#x2019;s latest anti-discrimination ordinance passed the Senate</a> &#x2026; <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20110512/SPORTS11/305120034/2275/rss05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Apparently you can fish with cicada</a>s?</li></ul><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Photo by </em><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/16828091@N04/5712462249/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\"><em>The Blonde Mule</em></a>.</p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2011/01/14/inauguration-day-road-closures/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Inauguration Day! [Road Closures]\">Inauguration Day! [Road Closures]</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2009/02/17/happy-hour-whos-your-american-idol/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Happy Hour: Who&#x2019;s Your American Idol?\">Happy Hour: Who&#x2019;s Your American Idol?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2010/12/03/on-the-day-of-the-nashville-christmas-parade-metro-gave-to-us-road-closures/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: On The Day Of The Nashville Christmas Parade, Metro Gave To Us [Road Closures]\">On The Day Of The Nashville Christmas Parade, Metro Gave To Us [Road Closures]</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}